{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id78b5fc1f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s825u"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"825u"},"text":"§ 825u.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Interest rate on power bonds held by Administrator of General Services","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Administrator of General Services or his successor in interest is authorized to reduce the rate of interest to 2½ per centum on all power bonds held by such Agency issued by States, public authorities, counties, municipalities, and other subdivisions of State governments for power projects financed by the Public Works Administration.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id78b5fc20-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-07-31/ch710/s6"},"text":"July 31, 1946, ch. 710, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/744"},"text":"60 Stat. 744","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-30/ch288"},"text":"June 30, 1949, ch. 288","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 103(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/380"},"text":"63 Stat. 380","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id78b5fc21-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id78b5fc22-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id78b5fc23-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section was not enacted as part of the Federal Power Act which generally comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id78b5fc24-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id78b5fc25-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions of Federal Works Agency and of all agencies thereof, together with functions of Federal Works Administrator, transferred to Administrator of General Services by section 103(a) of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1949","children":[],"tail":". Both Federal Works Agency and office of Federal Works Administrator abolished by section 103(b) of said act. See Historical and Revision Notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t40/s303/b"},"text":"section 303(b) of Title 40","children":[],"tail":", Public Buildings, Property, and Works. Transfer of functions of Federal Works Agency effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1949-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1949","children":[],"tail":", see section 605, formerly § 505, of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-06-30/ch288"},"text":"act June 30, 1949, ch. 288","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/403"},"text":"63 Stat. 403","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-05/ch849/s6/a"},"text":"act Sept. 5, 1950, ch. 849, § 6(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/583"},"text":"64 Stat. 583","children":[],"tail":". "},{